node.title: Tauranga retirement village staffer tests negative for COVID after positive rapid test result
node.description: They've received a negative PCR result.
node.content: ["A staff member at a Tauranga rest home who got a positive rapid antigen test (RaT) result for COVID-19 has received a negative nasal swab.\n", "Residents and families at Bob Owens Retirement Village were worried when a staff member got the positive RaT result on Tuesday.", "But late on Wednesday, the staffer received a negative PCR result.", "The team member has symptoms but was found to be suffering from another virus.", "All staff and residents in the hospital unit, where the staff member works, have had RaTs, with all returning negative results.", "They have also had nasal swabs.", "From Friday, the care centre will fully reopen, except for the hospital unit because they are still awaiting some nasal swab results.", "The retirement village includes townhouses, independent apartments or assisted-living apartments. It also has a care centre providing 122 care rooms offering rest home, hospital and specialist dementia care.", "RNZ"]
